2
00:00:17.058 --> 00:00:19.102
Dad.
you heard the doctors. right?

3
00:00:19.602 --> 00:00:23.314
There's still a long way to go.
but you've already improved a lot.

4
00:00:23.857 --> 00:00:24.982
What a relief.

5
00:00:24.983 --> 00:00:26.192
I can't walk.

6
00:00:27.402 --> 00:00:28.361
I can't work.

7
00:00:29.404 --> 00:00:31.114
I can't take care of you two.

8
00:00:31.656 --> 00:00:33.907
Oh. and my youngest. Bora...

9
00:00:33.908 --> 00:00:36.368
I told you not to worry about that.

10
00:00:36.369 --> 00:00:38.287
Bora is doing fine at Auntie's house.

11
00:00:38.288 --> 00:00:40.205
Don't worry about all those things.

12
00:00:40.206 --> 00:00:42.166
I'm already looking for a part-time job.

13
00:00:42.167 --> 00:00:44.626
No. no. You can't do
a part-time job. okay?

14
00:00:44.627 --> 00:00:49.924
If you really want to help me.
you focus on your studies.

15
00:00:50.467 --> 00:00:53.343
You can't let your grades fall
because of me.

16
00:00:55.430 --> 00:00:57.598
Hi.
Sorry. are we interrupting?

17
00:00:57.599 --> 00:00:59.433
- Not at all.
- Oh. hi.

18
00:00:59.434 --> 00:01:00.643
Hello.

19
00:01:01.936 --> 00:01:03.480
- Hello.
- You came!

20
00:01:04.522 --> 00:01:06.858
Mr. Kim. you look very good.

21
00:01:07.358 --> 00:01:09.026
We come bearing gifts.

22
00:01:09.027 --> 00:01:10.527
Oh.

23
00:01:10.528 --> 00:01:11.696
Oh. thank you.

24
00:01:12.405 --> 00:01:15.282
He's made so much progress
in the last two weeks.

25
00:01:15.283 --> 00:01:18.035
Hey. Min Ho.
I have a favor to ask you.

26
00:01:18.036 --> 00:01:20.330
If you ever hear Dae
talking nonsense about

27
00:01:20.872 --> 00:01:24.625
a part-time job.
you have to put a stop to it!

28
00:01:24.626 --> 00:01:28.754
Of course. don't worry.
I'll be sure to grab him if I hear of it.

29
00:01:28.755 --> 00:01:29.672
That's right.

30
00:01:30.256 --> 00:01:34.259
I feel better that Dae has
such a loyal and good friend like you.

31
00:01:35.804 --> 00:01:36.762
Thank you. sir.

32
00:01:39.933 --> 00:01:42.267
I think
she needs to check his vitals.

33
00:01:42.268 --> 00:01:45.145
We'll wait outside. Do you need anything?

34
00:01:51.569 --> 00:01:54.030
I thought things were
getting better with Dae.

35
00:01:54.531 --> 00:01:57.866
Well. at least
he's tolerating your presence now.

36
00:01:57.867 --> 00:01:59.827
- Mm-mm.
- I suppose.

37
00:01:59.828 --> 00:02:01.495
Any updates on cousin Jiwon?

38
00:02:01.496 --> 00:02:05.541
I've basically given up on that.
I mean. you saw how mad they were.

39
00:02:05.542 --> 00:02:06.875
Ugh.

40
00:02:06.876 --> 00:02:08.168
- What's up?
- Just...

41
00:02:08.169 --> 00:02:12.589
Jin's really stressed about the race
because his dad's gonna come watch.

42
00:02:12.590 --> 00:02:14.466
I don't know. I wish I could help him.

43
00:02:14.467 --> 00:02:18.804
What if you did something romantic
for him. just to take his mind off of it?

44
00:02:18.805 --> 00:02:21.391
Hmm. That's actually
a pretty good idea. Kitty.

45
00:02:23.059 --> 00:02:24.185
Hey. guys.

46
00:02:24.769 --> 00:02:26.729
Hey. Yuri.

47
00:02:28.314 --> 00:02:29.649
Kitty. can we talk?

48
00:02:30.900 --> 00:02:31.984
Um...

49
00:02:31.985 --> 00:02:35.571
- We're gonna go get some snacks.
- It's my intermittent fasting this week.

50
00:02:35.572 --> 00:02:36.698
Read the room.

51
00:02:38.825 --> 00:02:42.494
You haven't been answering
any of my texts. calls. DMs.

52
00:02:42.495 --> 00:02:45.247
Hmm. Don't you just hate
when that happens?

53
00:02:45.248 --> 00:02:49.001
Kitty. I'm so sorry I shut you out
while I was trying to get Juliana back.

54
00:02:49.002 --> 00:02:50.878
I just really miss our friendship.

55
00:02:53.256 --> 00:02:55.382
I have somewhere I need to be.

56
00:02:55.383 --> 00:02:57.176
Say bye to Mr. Kim for me. please.

57
00:02:59.429 --> 00:03:03.056
<i>I'm still really confused
about how to move forward with Yuri.</i>

58
00:03:03.057 --> 00:03:05.017
<i>And other things too. like.</i>

59
00:03:05.018 --> 00:03:09.479
<i>is my roommate Stella
the evil mastermind behind MoonLeaks?</i>

60
00:03:09.480 --> 00:03:11.231
<i>Luckily. when times are tough...</i>

61
00:03:11.232 --> 00:03:12.942
- Peter!
- There she is!

62
00:03:14.235 --> 00:03:16.904
<i>...there's nothing like
a friendly face from home.</i>

63
00:03:18.364 --> 00:03:19.616
I'm so happy you're here.

64
00:03:21.034 --> 00:03:22.076
Come on.

65
00:03:24.204 --> 00:03:27.998
<i>♪ I like me better when I'm with you ♪</i>

66
00:03:27.999 --> 00:03:31.126
Who knew people outside the States
cared about lacrosse?

67
00:03:31.127 --> 00:03:32.252
Okay.

68
00:03:32.253 --> 00:03:36.673
I'm not interrupting some weird
pre-tournament team ritual or anything?

69
00:03:36.674 --> 00:03:38.133
No. I'm all yours.

70
00:03:38.134 --> 00:03:39.801
Yay. I want to show you my dorm.

71
00:03:39.802 --> 00:03:41.178
Hell yeah.

72
00:03:41.179 --> 00:03:43.013
I can see why you like it here.

73
00:03:43.014 --> 00:03:46.934
God. it must be so crazy that you get
to walk in your mom's footsteps. huh?

74
00:03:46.935 --> 00:03:49.603
It's surreal. in the best way.

75
00:03:49.604 --> 00:03:54.984
You know. speaking of your mom. I am
under strict orders to hand-deliver these.

76
00:03:56.694 --> 00:04:00.530
Lara Jean found them at your grandma's.
They're letters Simon sent to your mom.

77
00:04:00.531 --> 00:04:02.366
Are you kidding me?

78
00:04:02.367 --> 00:04:03.618
Oh my God!

79
00:04:04.160 --> 00:04:06.203
I'm sure you're dying to rip into 'em.
so I figure...

80
00:04:06.204 --> 00:04:08.247
No. I am. trust me.
but I can do this later.

81
00:04:08.248 --> 00:04:10.207
I promised to help with a surprise for LJ.

82
00:04:10.208 --> 00:04:13.794
which. by the way.
what kind of surprise are we talking?

83
00:04:13.795 --> 00:04:17.297
It's not a ring. Kitty.
We are 22 years old.

84
00:04:17.298 --> 00:04:19.216
- I don't know!
- Yeesh.

85
00:04:19.217 --> 00:04:20.133
Hey.

86
00:04:20.134 --> 00:04:21.426
Hi.

87
00:04:21.427 --> 00:04:23.679
- Hi.
- Oh. you must be Peter.

88
00:04:23.680 --> 00:04:25.347
- Yes.
- I'm Juliana.

89
00:04:25.348 --> 00:04:26.473
One of my roommates.

90
00:04:26.474 --> 00:04:28.517
Yeah. Maybe don't swing by the dorm.

91
00:04:28.518 --> 00:04:31.187
unless you're trying
to introduce him to the Ohio weirdo.

92
00:04:32.355 --> 00:04:34.189
- It's nice meeting you though.
- You too.

93
00:04:36.985 --> 00:04:39.444
Okay. Lara Jean told me
you had beef with Juliana.

94
00:04:39.445 --> 00:04:41.029
but she was acting super chill.

95
00:04:41.030 --> 00:04:43.991
Well. we have a common enemy now.

96
00:04:43.992 --> 00:04:46.159
But I did still kiss
her girlfriend.

97
00:04:46.160 --> 00:04:47.119
Ex-girlfriend.

98
00:04:47.120 --> 00:04:49.246
Wait. Does that mean
there's a chance you and Yuri--

99
00:04:49.247 --> 00:04:53.709
No. No chance. And I wouldn't want
a chance. given the way she treated me.

100
00:04:53.710 --> 00:04:57.963
Okay. so Yuri's out. We're canceling Yuri.
What about the guy on the plane?

101
00:04:57.964 --> 00:05:01.258
No. he's dating our other roommate.
the Ohio weirdo. Stella.

102
00:05:01.259 --> 00:05:02.884
Anyway. let's go. This way.

103
00:05:02.885 --> 00:05:05.762
I wanna know why you guys are calling
a human being "the Ohio weirdo."

104
00:05:05.763 --> 00:05:08.640
I think she's using Min Ho
to bring down his famous dad.

105
00:05:08.641 --> 00:05:10.767
See. she snuck into his office.
and then...

106
00:05:10.768 --> 00:05:12.311
Never mind. You'll think I'm insane.

107
00:05:12.312 --> 00:05:14.896
Oh no. you're definitely insane.

108
00:05:17.817 --> 00:05:19.401
<i>♪ I feel like I know it ♪</i>

109
00:05:19.402 --> 00:05:21.486
<i>♪ Baby. when I look at you ♪</i>

110
00:05:21.487 --> 00:05:22.696
<i>♪ I'm in love ♪</i>

111
00:05:25.992 --> 00:05:27.744
- Isn't it great?
- Yes.

112
00:05:28.244 --> 00:05:30.412
Ah. I want everything.

113
00:05:30.413 --> 00:05:35.542
Okay. so which of these do you think
your sister is gonna like...

114
00:05:35.543 --> 00:05:37.210
Never mind. What? I'm gonna get 'em all.

115
00:05:37.211 --> 00:05:39.087
You are such a simp for LJ.

116
00:05:39.088 --> 00:05:42.717
Hey. I am not a... Oh yes! Look at these.

117
00:05:43.426 --> 00:05:46.595
Oh yeah. she's going to love these.

118
00:05:46.596 --> 00:05:47.638
Covey?

119
00:05:48.306 --> 00:05:49.264
Min Ho.

120
00:05:49.265 --> 00:05:51.516
- The guy from the plane?
- Stop talking.

121
00:05:51.517 --> 00:05:54.228
- What are you doing here?
- Stella. She loves this place.

122
00:05:55.355 --> 00:05:57.732
- Peter Kavinsky.
- All right. mate?

123
00:05:58.358 --> 00:06:00.192
- Yeah.
- This is Lara Jean's boyfriend.

124
00:06:00.193 --> 00:06:01.568
- My sister.
- I know.

125
00:06:01.569 --> 00:06:05.489
I was subject to your monologues
for an entire semester. remember?

126
00:06:05.490 --> 00:06:06.990
I heard about your travel too.

127
00:06:06.991 --> 00:06:09.494
- Hmm.
- In great detail. actually. from Covey.

128
00:06:10.286 --> 00:06:12.704
You're here for what?
A ping-pong tournament?

129
00:06:12.705 --> 00:06:15.374
- Lacrosse.
- Yeah. same thing.

130
00:06:15.375 --> 00:06:18.627
Uh. those sparkly pens are super sick.
Where did you find those?

131
00:06:18.628 --> 00:06:22.339
Thanks. It's actually
right by the sparkly stickers.

132
00:06:22.340 --> 00:06:23.383
Mm.

133
00:06:24.425 --> 00:06:26.635
- Thanks. bro.
- No worries. mate.

134
00:06:26.636 --> 00:06:27.595
Covey.

135
00:06:30.640 --> 00:06:32.766
You know. I think
he totally likes you still.

136
00:06:32.767 --> 00:06:36.311
- Whoa. Whoa. no. Nope.
- He's calling you by your last name.

137
00:06:36.312 --> 00:06:39.523
- That's not a thing. Peter.
- He remembers every word you've ever said.

138
00:06:39.524 --> 00:06:43.360
But he still pretends to be annoyed
when you talk too much. Classic.

139
00:06:43.361 --> 00:06:46.530
He has a girlfriend who he's very into.
Did you see the sparkly pens?

140
00:06:46.531 --> 00:06:48.740
But I'm telling you.
she's up to something.

141
00:06:48.741 --> 00:06:52.119
Only I can't prove it without
looking like a freak and butting in.

142
00:06:52.120 --> 00:06:56.999
Okay. well. look. if he is your friend.
then you should look out for him.

143
00:06:57.708 --> 00:06:58.543
Yeah.

144
00:06:59.043 --> 00:07:02.129
Also. since when do you care
about looking like a freak?

145
00:07:02.130 --> 00:07:03.505
All right. I gotta get going.

146
00:07:03.506 --> 00:07:07.551
But I do have a free window
this Saturday before we leave for Tokyo.

147
00:07:07.552 --> 00:07:08.844
With enough time to try

148
00:07:08.845 --> 00:07:10.762
a sweet potato latte
from our coffee truck?

149
00:07:10.763 --> 00:07:12.181
Can't say no to that.

150
00:07:12.723 --> 00:07:14.141
Or a Covey sister.

151
00:07:14.142 --> 00:07:15.101
Yay.

152
00:07:15.768 --> 00:07:17.270
Can I also have this one?

153
00:07:17.979 --> 00:07:19.855
- Excellent choice.
- Thank you.

154
00:07:19.856 --> 00:07:20.898
Hello.

155
00:07:30.116 --> 00:07:32.409
<i>"Dear Eve. Hello from Korea."</i>

156
00:07:32.410 --> 00:07:35.162
<i>"Happy Lunar New Year 1994."</i>

157
00:07:35.163 --> 00:07:36.997
<i>"Sorry your mom's still mad at you."</i>

158
00:07:36.998 --> 00:07:40.543
<i>"I feel somewhat responsible
for dragging you into this family feud."</i>

159
00:07:41.836 --> 00:07:44.046
Jeez. Grandma. way to hold a grudge.

160
00:07:46.257 --> 00:07:49.342
<i>"Dear Eve.
Dan sounds cool for a white guy.</i>

161
00:07:49.343 --> 00:07:51.052
<i>and you seem head over heels."</i>

162
00:07:51.053 --> 00:07:54.431
<i>"Did you hear your old friend Gina
has a new boyfriend too?"</i>

163
00:07:54.432 --> 00:07:56.391
<i>"Sun-jin Han. total player.</i>

164
00:07:56.392 --> 00:07:59.144
<i>and I'm pretty sure
she's not his only girlfriend."</i>

165
00:07:59.145 --> 00:08:02.272
<i>"I can't believe you convinced
your mother to go back to Korea."</i>

166
00:08:02.273 --> 00:08:03.857
<i>"Remember back in the '90s</i>

167
00:08:03.858 --> 00:08:06.735
<i>when she didn't speak to you
for six months because of this?"</i>

168
00:08:06.736 --> 00:08:08.778
<i>"Now I just have to get my mom on board."</i>

169
00:08:08.779 --> 00:08:09.905
Wait. what?

170
00:08:09.906 --> 00:08:12.365
<i>"And I'm so happy
you're bringing your youngest."</i>

171
00:08:12.366 --> 00:08:15.869
<i>"How cool that Kitty will have her first
passport stamp at three years old."</i>

172
00:08:15.870 --> 00:08:17.871
<i>"Jiwon can't wait
to play with her cousin."</i>

173
00:08:17.872 --> 00:08:19.290
Oh my God.

174
00:08:24.337 --> 00:08:25.295
Kitty?

175
00:08:25.296 --> 00:08:28.173
<i>I'm still feeling weird about us.
but I just had to tell you.</i>

176
00:08:28.174 --> 00:08:31.426
My sister's boyfriend gave me a bunch
of letters from Simon to my mom.

177
00:08:31.427 --> 00:08:34.137
<i>It turns out they were
writing each other for years.</i>

178
00:08:34.138 --> 00:08:36.139
And I found out my mom
convinced my grandma

179
00:08:36.140 --> 00:08:38.225
to reunite with her sister
when I was little.

180
00:08:38.226 --> 00:08:40.978
She was gonna bring me
to Korea too. but she...

181
00:08:44.482 --> 00:08:45.816
But she died before...

182
00:08:48.069 --> 00:08:49.361
Before we could go.

183
00:08:49.362 --> 00:08:51.905
<i>I was meant to be part of their reunion.</i>

184
00:08:51.906 --> 00:08:53.698
<i>Oh. Kitty.</i>

185
00:08:53.699 --> 00:08:57.410
Only no. because I'm stuck.

186
00:08:57.411 --> 00:08:59.412
My great-aunt won't let me in the house.

187
00:08:59.413 --> 00:09:02.708
and my cousin Jiwon
has ghosted me on Instagram. so...

188
00:09:03.209 --> 00:09:04.960
<i>Well. what can I do to help?</i>

189
00:09:06.587 --> 00:09:07.880
I don't...

190
00:09:08.756 --> 00:09:10.840
I don't really know how you can.

191
00:09:10.841 --> 00:09:12.342
<i>But thanks for listening.</i>

192
00:09:19.767 --> 00:09:24.437
Luckily for you. this non-pop quiz
is worth only 5% of your final grade.

193
00:09:24.438 --> 00:09:27.275
The earlier you start reviewing
for the final. the better.

194
00:09:30.194 --> 00:09:31.987
That bloke bought you a pen?

195
00:09:31.988 --> 00:09:34.030
What's his name? Pete?

196
00:09:34.031 --> 00:09:36.284
Peter. And... yeah.

197
00:09:37.535 --> 00:09:39.703
I'm sure Stella also loved her pen.

198
00:09:39.704 --> 00:09:42.498
<i>And is using it to write up
her next diabolical plan.</i>

199
00:09:43.249 --> 00:09:45.333
Did you guys go on
some hot date last night?

200
00:09:45.334 --> 00:09:47.336
She barely made it home for curfew check.

201
00:09:48.421 --> 00:09:50.214
None of your business. Covey.

202
00:09:56.387 --> 00:09:59.723
Um. Professor Lee. are there
any TA positions available?

203
00:09:59.724 --> 00:10:01.266
I could really use the money.

204
00:10:01.267 --> 00:10:03.977
Unfortunately. in light of
the MoonLeaks scandal.

205
00:10:03.978 --> 00:10:07.772
the school's been under a lot of heat.
We're bracing for potential budget cuts.

206
00:10:07.773 --> 00:10:09.859
I... I understand. Thank you.

207
00:10:14.447 --> 00:10:16.406
Speaking of MoonLeaks. Min Ho!

208
00:10:16.407 --> 00:10:18.825
Can you please let your father know
that a PR crisis

209
00:10:18.826 --> 00:10:21.370
is not a reason to call off
weeks of classes?

210
00:10:22.747 --> 00:10:23.748
Will do.

211
00:10:24.498 --> 00:10:26.083
I don't believe you.

212
00:10:27.209 --> 00:10:28.127
Dae.

213
00:10:28.919 --> 00:10:31.254
I heard you ask Lee for a job.

214
00:10:31.255 --> 00:10:33.341
I promised your dad
I wouldn't let you do that.

215
00:10:34.175 --> 00:10:36.635
- If you need money. I can always--
- Dae!

216
00:10:36.636 --> 00:10:37.552
Yes. sir.

217
00:10:37.553 --> 00:10:39.512
"Sir"?
Can you believe this kid?

218
00:10:39.513 --> 00:10:41.473
Could you excuse us for a minute?

219
00:10:43.017 --> 00:10:44.268
Dae. seriously!

220
00:10:45.061 --> 00:10:45.977
Where have you been?

221
00:10:45.978 --> 00:10:47.145
Handling MoonLeaks.

222
00:10:47.146 --> 00:10:51.107
I fired several executives. and I had
everyone else sign an iron-clad NDA.

223
00:10:51.108 --> 00:10:52.192
It's behind us.

224
00:10:52.193 --> 00:10:54.569
I hope it didn't have
any negative effect on you.

225
00:10:54.570 --> 00:10:55.945
Oh. not at all.

226
00:10:55.946 --> 00:10:59.783
I've only been pestered by hundreds
of people on every social media platform.

227
00:10:59.784 --> 00:11:01.826
dying to know if you're a sociopath.

228
00:11:01.827 --> 00:11:03.787
Or if you have hair plugs.

229
00:11:03.788 --> 00:11:06.081
Well. I'm about to change
the conversation.

230
00:11:06.082 --> 00:11:09.000
Tonight. I am gathering my best students

231
00:11:09.001 --> 00:11:11.169
to discuss the future
of the Moon Arts Program.

232
00:11:11.170 --> 00:11:15.131
Dad. it's Friday. <i>Bulgeum</i>.
I obviously have plans with my girlfriend.

233
00:11:15.132 --> 00:11:18.969
Oh. She's invited. of course.
I promise. it will be worth it.

234
00:11:19.512 --> 00:11:21.847
Fine. I'll be there.

235
00:11:28.479 --> 00:11:30.523
Thanks for doing this. I...

236
00:11:31.399 --> 00:11:33.359
I know this has been hard for you.

237
00:11:33.984 --> 00:11:35.819
It could have been you running tomorrow.

238
00:11:35.820 --> 00:11:37.737
If I had only known then

239
00:11:37.738 --> 00:11:40.281
how I was gonna feel
about you now. I wouldn't have--

240
00:11:40.282 --> 00:11:41.242
It's okay.

241
00:11:41.992 --> 00:11:42.827
Really.

242
00:11:44.870 --> 00:11:46.413
Something I've been meaning to ask you...

243
00:11:46.414 --> 00:11:49.833
Since my dad is going to be at regionals.
would you want to meet him?

244
00:11:49.834 --> 00:11:51.919
<i>The</i> Mr. Olympics?

245
00:11:52.753 --> 00:11:53.837
I would love that.

246
00:11:55.756 --> 00:11:58.259
Okay. I should probably
do a couple more sprints.

247
00:11:59.343 --> 00:12:01.761
Or... want to race?

248
00:12:01.762 --> 00:12:03.638
Oh. it's so on.

249
00:12:03.639 --> 00:12:05.808
The loser has to do 100 burpees.

250
00:12:07.309 --> 00:12:08.853
What's the matter? Can't keep up?

251
00:12:13.399 --> 00:12:15.108
Shit. shit. shit. Are you okay?

252
00:12:15.109 --> 00:12:16.651
Just rolled my ankle. I'm fine.

253
00:12:16.652 --> 00:12:19.864
- That did not sound fine. You need--
- I said I'm fine!

254
00:12:21.407 --> 00:12:23.492
See? Just need to sleep it off.

255
00:12:41.218 --> 00:12:43.429
Whoa! Such a vibe!

256
00:12:44.972 --> 00:12:45.848
What?

257
00:12:48.642 --> 00:12:51.686
Do you think he's gonna have to sell
all that crap when his empire tanks?

258
00:12:51.687 --> 00:12:53.146
- Dude!
- What?

259
00:12:53.147 --> 00:12:56.900
Welcome. welcome. My best students
in Entertainment Management.

260
00:12:56.901 --> 00:12:59.486
And the star of
my Acting for K Drama class.

261
00:12:59.487 --> 00:13:01.613
- What?
- Come on in. Come on in. please.

262
00:13:01.614 --> 00:13:03.115
- Thank you.
- Come on in.

263
00:13:03.824 --> 00:13:05.074
For the host.

264
00:13:05.075 --> 00:13:07.453
Oh. Oh. a gift.

265
00:13:08.412 --> 00:13:09.246
Yeah.

266
00:13:12.041 --> 00:13:13.374
Oh.

267
00:13:13.375 --> 00:13:14.877
Thank you. son.

268
00:13:16.962 --> 00:13:18.756
I know the perfect place for it.

269
00:13:19.423 --> 00:13:20.632
You're welcome. Dad.

270
00:13:20.633 --> 00:13:22.592
I'm very touched.

271
00:13:22.593 --> 00:13:23.761
Excuse me.

272
00:13:25.721 --> 00:13:27.263
That's... odd.

273
00:13:27.264 --> 00:13:31.559
Is it me. or did he just exhibit
a genuine human emotion?

274
00:13:31.560 --> 00:13:33.896
You should probably go check on him.

275
00:13:42.196 --> 00:13:43.072
Dad?

276
00:13:44.615 --> 00:13:46.075
Is everything all right?

277
00:13:50.621 --> 00:13:52.581
What have I done with my life. Min Ho?

278
00:13:53.123 --> 00:13:55.250
I barely know my own kids
except as commodities.

279
00:13:55.251 --> 00:13:58.545
And you. I want to be in your life.

280
00:13:58.546 --> 00:14:00.214
Then you might've shown up at <i>Seollal</i>.

281
00:14:00.798 --> 00:14:02.841
Your brother's in trouble. He needs me.

282
00:14:04.343 --> 00:14:06.094
Joon Ho got a girl pregnant.

283
00:14:06.095 --> 00:14:08.179
Some backup dancer.

284
00:14:08.180 --> 00:14:12.600
- That's why you missed the ski cabin.
- Yeah. Stress is getting to him.

285
00:14:12.601 --> 00:14:15.896
He's having panic attacks.
and he's even talking about quitting.

286
00:14:16.522 --> 00:14:17.815
You can't tell anyone.

287
00:14:18.315 --> 00:14:19.440
I won't.

288
00:14:19.441 --> 00:14:22.318
I know it's terrible timing
with the MoonLeaks scandal.

289
00:14:22.319 --> 00:14:26.657
If I lose my biggest star.
it's over. and I'll have nothing.

290
00:14:30.953 --> 00:14:32.079
That's not true. Dad.

291
00:14:34.456 --> 00:14:38.627
I made mistakes. and it means a lot
that you showed up for me tonight.

292
00:14:48.846 --> 00:14:50.680
Kitty? You're kind of staring.

293
00:14:50.681 --> 00:14:53.892
Oh no. I was just admiring your makeup.
I've never been good at contour.

294
00:14:53.893 --> 00:14:55.185
Hmm.

295
00:14:55.686 --> 00:14:57.270
Where did you get your nose done?

296
00:14:57.271 --> 00:14:58.563
Excuse me?

297
00:14:58.564 --> 00:15:00.941
Oh no. don't misunderstand.
It's really nice.

298
00:15:01.442 --> 00:15:02.692
Uh...

299
00:15:02.693 --> 00:15:04.236
God gave me this nose.

300
00:15:05.738 --> 00:15:06.614
Sorry!

301
00:15:07.740 --> 00:15:09.949
My bad.

302
00:15:09.950 --> 00:15:13.787
She's totally lying.
I know a rhinoplasty when I see one.

303
00:15:14.496 --> 00:15:17.582
- Interesting.
- Wanna know who else at school has one?

304
00:15:17.583 --> 00:15:20.377
I'm... I'm good. for now.

305
00:15:21.003 --> 00:15:22.004
Okay.

306
00:15:28.218 --> 00:15:29.886
Pretty nice place. huh?

307
00:15:29.887 --> 00:15:31.220
Seriously.

308
00:15:31.221 --> 00:15:33.139
There are no skyscrapers in Pepper Pike.

309
00:15:35.476 --> 00:15:37.144
- Hello. darling.
- Hi.

310
00:15:39.063 --> 00:15:40.897
You were right. as usual.

311
00:15:40.898 --> 00:15:42.941
I'm glad I went over to talk to him.

312
00:15:42.942 --> 00:15:44.568
She was right about what?

313
00:15:45.653 --> 00:15:47.988
Everyone. dinner is served.

314
00:15:56.288 --> 00:15:57.373
Yes?

315
00:15:58.207 --> 00:16:01.167
Hello. I know you don't know me.
but my name is--

316
00:16:01.168 --> 00:16:02.126
Yuri Han.

317
00:16:02.127 --> 00:16:05.797
I follow you on Insta.
I loved your last "Get Ready With Me."

318
00:16:05.798 --> 00:16:07.674
Oh. That's the same bag.

319
00:16:07.675 --> 00:16:08.967
Oh.

320
00:16:08.968 --> 00:16:12.512
Great. Then maybe
you'll listen to what I have to say

321
00:16:12.513 --> 00:16:14.640
and stop ghosting my friend Kitty.

322
00:16:17.017 --> 00:16:19.686
All right.
So I hope everyone enjoyed the meal.

323
00:16:19.687 --> 00:16:21.229
And I have an announcement.

324
00:16:21.230 --> 00:16:24.399
As you know. my big showcase
is coming up soon. but--

325
00:16:24.400 --> 00:16:27.402
Oh no. Has it been canceled
because of MoonLeaks?

326
00:16:27.403 --> 00:16:29.779
Oh. of course not.
We are going even bigger.

327
00:16:29.780 --> 00:16:32.865
And no one will remember MoonLeaks
after what I am planning.

328
00:16:32.866 --> 00:16:36.661
Our showcase will now be filmed
at one of Seoul's grand palaces

329
00:16:36.662 --> 00:16:38.496
and streamed around the world.

330
00:16:38.497 --> 00:16:42.792
We are turning this into
a massive reality competition show.

331
00:16:42.793 --> 00:16:44.669
You know.
I've had many shows over the years.

332
00:16:44.670 --> 00:16:46.754
<i>International Star Challenge
with Young Moon.</i>

333
00:16:46.755 --> 00:16:48.840
<i>Land Amongst the Stars with Young Moon.</i>

334
00:16:48.841 --> 00:16:50.758
and my highest rated of all.

335
00:16:50.759 --> 00:16:52.385
<i>Rising Stars with Young Moon.</i>

336
00:16:52.386 --> 00:16:55.471
Sorry.

337
00:16:55.472 --> 00:16:58.266
It's okay. So. we'll have
a special performance by Joon Ho.

338
00:16:58.267 --> 00:17:00.435
And the winner

339
00:17:00.436 --> 00:17:03.312
will get a recording contract
with Moon Star Entertainment.

340
00:17:03.313 --> 00:17:05.106
No way.

341
00:17:05.107 --> 00:17:08.401
Now. this competition
will be for solo artists only.

342
00:17:08.402 --> 00:17:09.986
A K-pop duo is a no-go.

343
00:17:09.987 --> 00:17:12.405
Sorry. you two. You'll have to split up.

344
00:17:12.406 --> 00:17:16.951
Now. let's eat dessert. and then I have
the best karaoke setup in all of Seoul.

345
00:17:16.952 --> 00:17:19.037
Oh. dear Lord.

346
00:17:19.038 --> 00:17:26.045
<i>♪ I thank God every day
That I woke up feeling this way ♪</i>

347
00:17:26.837 --> 00:17:30.089
<i>♪ If I was you. I'd wanna be me too ♪</i>

348
00:17:30.090 --> 00:17:34.510
<i>♪ I'd wanna be me too
I'd wanna be me too ♪</i>

349
00:17:34.511 --> 00:17:37.847
<i>♪ If I was you. I'd wanna be me too ♪</i>

350
00:17:37.848 --> 00:17:38.890
<i>♪ I'd wanna... ♪</i>

351
00:17:38.891 --> 00:17:40.850
What's wrong?
What's the problem?

352
00:17:40.851 --> 00:17:42.352
The hospital contacted me

353
00:17:42.978 --> 00:17:46.189
and said the Han Group
is not paying my dad's medical bills.

354
00:17:46.190 --> 00:17:48.274
I'll ask my dad.

355
00:17:48.275 --> 00:17:49.318
Forget it.

356
00:17:50.110 --> 00:17:52.361
How can you.
knowing your dad's company is in trouble?

357
00:17:52.362 --> 00:17:54.989
Then I'll take some from my savings.

358
00:17:54.990 --> 00:17:56.699
This is more important.

359
00:17:56.700 --> 00:18:00.537
Is this you trying
to buy my forgiveness?

360
00:18:02.331 --> 00:18:03.332
No.

361
00:18:04.208 --> 00:18:05.041
Maybe.

362
00:18:12.508 --> 00:18:15.594
- Is that a cheeky little smile I see?
- Shut up.

363
00:18:16.678 --> 00:18:19.222
Anyway. I can't take
that much money from you.

364
00:18:19.223 --> 00:18:24.103
And I know
that you regret what you did.

365
00:18:25.104 --> 00:18:26.188
I do.

366
00:18:28.732 --> 00:18:30.567
There's nothing between me and Covey.

367
00:18:32.444 --> 00:18:33.402
Yeah.

368
00:18:36.240 --> 00:18:39.367
<i>♪ I'd wanna be me too ♪</i>

369
00:18:42.287 --> 00:18:44.330
Ah. that record deal
my dad's offering!

370
00:18:44.331 --> 00:18:45.540
If you do well.

371
00:18:45.541 --> 00:18:48.335
that could help pay off
your dad's hospital bills.

372
00:18:49.378 --> 00:18:51.880
- If you win. that is.
- Yeah.

373
00:18:52.798 --> 00:18:54.424
You know what? Never mind.

374
00:18:55.217 --> 00:18:57.135
You will win. with my help.

375
00:18:57.136 --> 00:18:59.513
Come on. Dae. One last duet?

376
00:19:02.558 --> 00:19:04.892
I'm going to try
to win that record deal.

377
00:19:04.893 --> 00:19:06.394
Me too.

378
00:19:06.395 --> 00:19:07.938
Are you confident?

379
00:19:08.981 --> 00:19:11.066
<i>♪ Don't go breaking my heart ♪</i>

380
00:19:12.401 --> 00:19:15.027
<i>♪ I couldn't if I tried ♪</i>

381
00:19:15.028 --> 00:19:16.488
<i>♪ Hey. hey! ♪</i>

382
00:19:19.658 --> 00:19:22.744
<i>That's weird.
Who hates karaoke this much?</i>

383
00:19:23.370 --> 00:19:26.164
Stella! Why don't you come up here?

384
00:19:26.165 --> 00:19:27.248
We could do a duet.

385
00:19:27.249 --> 00:19:29.375
Oh. that's... that's okay.

386
00:19:29.376 --> 00:19:31.794
No. girl. didn't you sing
in your church choir?

387
00:19:31.795 --> 00:19:33.088
Come on. Don't be shy. Come on.

388
00:19:33.672 --> 00:19:35.257
I need some water.

389
00:19:37.676 --> 00:19:40.803
<i>♪ Go on now. go
Walk out the door ♪</i>

390
00:19:43.098 --> 00:19:45.433
<i>First.
Stella does a literal spit take</i>

391
00:19:45.434 --> 00:19:48.060
<i>when Moon mentions
one of his old reality shows.</i>

392
00:19:48.061 --> 00:19:50.396
<i>Then she freaks out at karaoke.</i>

393
00:19:50.397 --> 00:19:52.773
<i>Two huge red flags.</i>

394
00:19:52.774 --> 00:19:57.279
<i>Rising Stars with Young Moon.</i>

395
00:19:58.238 --> 00:19:59.363
Mm.

396
00:19:59.364 --> 00:20:01.742
Pepper Pike. Ohio.

397
00:20:08.540 --> 00:20:12.252
Oh. My. God.

398
00:20:16.757 --> 00:20:18.090
Are you sure you're okay?

399
00:20:18.091 --> 00:20:20.260
For the last time. yes.

400
00:20:21.720 --> 00:20:23.596
Jin! Mate. what's wrong?

401
00:20:23.597 --> 00:20:25.473
- Did you tell him?
- No. why would I?

402
00:20:25.474 --> 00:20:27.475
What have you done?
You're clearly injured.

403
00:20:27.476 --> 00:20:29.852
I can see it plain as day. Your ankle.

404
00:20:29.853 --> 00:20:31.395
Coach. I'm fine. I can run.

405
00:20:31.396 --> 00:20:32.939
Jin. I'm sorry. You're out.

406
00:20:32.940 --> 00:20:35.399
Q? You're in.

407
00:20:35.400 --> 00:20:38.862
I need you to go to the lockers and grab
your spikes before the bus gets here.

408
00:20:41.657 --> 00:20:43.325
You heard him. Go.

409
00:20:47.537 --> 00:20:49.081
<i>♪ Clap ♪</i>

410
00:20:52.125 --> 00:20:54.044
<i>♪ I don't care anymore ♪</i>

411
00:20:55.087 --> 00:20:56.003
<i>♪ Oh. yeah ♪</i>

412
00:21:21.238 --> 00:21:24.032
Jiwon just DMed me. She wants to meet up.

413
00:21:25.242 --> 00:21:28.369
Aww. That is so amazing.
I'm so happy for you.

414
00:21:28.370 --> 00:21:29.454
Thank you.

415
00:21:30.622 --> 00:21:34.625
Wait. guys. look. That's Q.
I didn't know he was running.

416
00:21:34.626 --> 00:21:36.503
Q? Where's Jin?

417
00:21:39.506 --> 00:21:41.258
<i>Runners. on your marks!</i>

418
00:21:44.011 --> 00:21:44.885
<i>Get set!</i>

419
00:21:47.097 --> 00:21:48.890
<i>Go!</i>

420
00:21:51.143 --> 00:21:53.019
Drive! Come on. Q!

421
00:21:53.020 --> 00:21:54.938
- Let's go!
- Let's get it!

422
00:21:58.275 --> 00:21:59.568
Let's go!

423
00:22:02.195 --> 00:22:03.946
<i>KISS in first place!</i>

424
00:22:06.533 --> 00:22:07.492
Yeah!

425
00:22:31.683 --> 00:22:33.101
Min Ho. wait up!

426
00:22:33.894 --> 00:22:36.146
I need to talk to you.

427
00:22:36.646 --> 00:22:39.232
- Come on.
- What are you doing?

428
00:22:39.816 --> 00:22:42.027
Stella is not who you think she is.

429
00:22:43.612 --> 00:22:47.615
<i>♪ Amazing Grace ♪</i>

430
00:22:47.616 --> 00:22:51.702
<i>♪ How sweet the sound ♪</i>

431
00:22:51.703 --> 00:22:55.581
<i>♪ That saved a wretch ♪</i>

432
00:22:55.582 --> 00:22:58.250
<i>♪ Like me ♪</i>

433
00:22:58.251 --> 00:23:00.796
<i>♪ I once was-- ♪</i>

434
00:23:02.005 --> 00:23:04.673
- Why are you showing me this?
- Keep watching.

435
00:23:04.674 --> 00:23:06.300
<i>♪ I see ♪</i>

436
00:23:06.301 --> 00:23:07.676
<i>Wow.</i>

437
00:23:07.677 --> 00:23:10.763
<i>Esther from Ohio.
I have goosebumps all over.</i>

438
00:23:10.764 --> 00:23:14.934
<i>Thank you. Mr. Moon.
That means everything coming from you.</i>

439
00:23:14.935 --> 00:23:20.857
<i>Unfortunately. to be a real star. you need
the look. which you just don't have.</i>

440
00:23:21.441 --> 00:23:22.566
<i>Pass.</i>

441
00:23:25.112 --> 00:23:29.116
<i>But beauty is
supposed to come from within.</i>

442
00:23:30.117 --> 00:23:32.201
That girl is Stella!

443
00:23:32.202 --> 00:23:35.746
What are you talking about?
It says her name is Esther Shim.

444
00:23:35.747 --> 00:23:39.458
Yeah. from Pepper Pike. Ohio.
who grew up singing in the church.

445
00:23:39.459 --> 00:23:41.001
- You're insane.
- No. listen to me.

446
00:23:41.002 --> 00:23:43.588
This became a meme. It was a viral video.

447
00:23:45.340 --> 00:23:51.011
<i>But beauty is
supposed to come from within!</i>

448
00:23:52.556 --> 00:23:53.556
<i>♪ Amazing Grace... ♪</i>

449
00:23:53.557 --> 00:23:55.266
It's her.

450
00:23:55.267 --> 00:24:00.354
Yeah. she changed her name and changed
her face. but that's Stella's voice.

451
00:24:00.355 --> 00:24:02.064
Look. I feel bad for her.

452
00:24:02.065 --> 00:24:05.443
I mean. she was a middle schooler
who got bullied by the entire internet.

453
00:24:05.444 --> 00:24:07.736
but now it's her motive--

454
00:24:07.737 --> 00:24:09.071
Motive?

455
00:24:09.072 --> 00:24:12.992
Stella leaked my letter as a distraction
so she could sneak into your dad's office

456
00:24:12.993 --> 00:24:15.911
to find dirt on him.
And then MoonLeaks dropped.

457
00:24:15.912 --> 00:24:18.038
I'm telling you.
she wants revenge on your dad

458
00:24:18.039 --> 00:24:21.585
and she's using
your fake relationship as a cover.

459
00:24:22.752 --> 00:24:25.629
First of all.
she's on good terms with my dad.

460
00:24:25.630 --> 00:24:29.049
She even got me a gift for him.
You have no idea how happy that made him

461
00:24:29.050 --> 00:24:32.303
or what it means to me
to have a better relationship with him.

462
00:24:32.304 --> 00:24:35.806
And second of all.
not everyone is in a fake relationship.

463
00:24:35.807 --> 00:24:38.142
- No. not everyone. Stella.
- Enough!

464
00:24:38.143 --> 00:24:42.105
It was bad enough you broke my heart.
You trying to break up my relationship?

465
00:24:42.772 --> 00:24:44.357
I... broke your heart?

466
00:24:48.612 --> 00:24:52.198
Why do you think I jumped into
a rebound relationship with Stella?

467
00:24:52.199 --> 00:24:55.576
And now that I'm past all that
and actually really care about her.

468
00:24:55.577 --> 00:24:57.411
you try to tear us apart because what?

469
00:24:57.412 --> 00:24:58.787
Are you jealous or something?

470
00:24:58.788 --> 00:25:00.789
You're my friend.
I wanna look out for you.

471
00:25:00.790 --> 00:25:02.042
Well. don't!

472
00:25:06.922 --> 00:25:09.381
Maybe Min Ho just needs
time to process.

473
00:25:09.382 --> 00:25:10.759
It's a lot to handle.

474
00:25:11.635 --> 00:25:13.511
I've never seen him
so angry before.

475
00:25:13.512 --> 00:25:16.138
When am I gonna learn
to just mind my own business?

476
00:25:16.139 --> 00:25:18.807
All I do is ruin things
for myself and for other people.

477
00:25:18.808 --> 00:25:20.894
Hey. that is not true.

478
00:25:21.478 --> 00:25:24.021
Remember when you mailed out
Lara Jean's love letters?

479
00:25:24.022 --> 00:25:27.358
You not minding your business
landed me the love of my life.

480
00:25:27.359 --> 00:25:30.653
Kitty. you have this killer instinct.

481
00:25:30.654 --> 00:25:33.073
It is literally your superpower.

482
00:25:34.407 --> 00:25:36.283
So stop second-guessing yourself.

483
00:25:36.284 --> 00:25:39.954
Who cares if Min Ho wasn't ready
to hear what you had to say?

484
00:25:39.955 --> 00:25:41.581
It doesn't mean you're wrong.

485
00:25:43.208 --> 00:25:44.209
Thank you. Peter.

486
00:25:47.462 --> 00:25:50.507
You are Kitty Song Fricking Covey.

487
00:25:51.550 --> 00:25:53.093
Don't you forget it.

488
00:25:54.678 --> 00:25:57.054
- You're the best.
